The paper deals with logical properties of nonmonotonic consequence relations, which is a topic in the subfield of computer science known as Logic and Computation (cs.LO). The paper also discusses Social Choice, which is a topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper touches on Game Theory (cs.GT) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) as it discusses the soundness of the result. Finally, the paper deals with sets of models, which is a topic in Data Structures (cs.DS).
